  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Mourning over the Locust Plague'
      title: Mourning over the Locust Plague
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave this message to Joel son of
        Pethuel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Hear this, you leaders of the people.Listen, all who live in the
        land.In all your history,has anything like this happened before?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Tell your children about it in the years to come,and let your children
        tell their children.Pass the story down from generation to generation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'After the cutting locusts finished eating the crops,the swarming
        locusts took what was left!After them came the hopping locusts,and then the
        stripping locusts,[[COMMENT(0)]] too!  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:4 '
        content: The precise identification of the four kinds of locusts mentioned
          here is uncertain.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Wake up, you drunkards, and weep!Wail, all you wine-drinkers!All
        the grapes are ruined,and all your sweet wine is gone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "A vast army of locusts[[COMMENT(0)]] has invaded my land,a terrible
        army too numerous to count.Its teeth are like lions\u2019 teeth,its fangs
        like those of a lioness.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>A nation.</b>
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'It has destroyed my grapevinesand ruined my fig trees,stripping their
        bark and destroying it,leaving the branches white and bare.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Weep like a bride dressed in black,mourning the death of her husband.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For there is no grain or wineto offer at the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.So
        the priests are in mourning.The ministers of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        are weeping.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The fields are ruined,the land is stripped bare.The grain is destroyed,the
        grapes have shriveled,and the olive oil is gone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Despair, all you farmers!Wail, all you vine growers!Weep, because
        the wheat and barley\u2014all the crops of the field\u2014are ruined.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The grapevines have dried up,and the fig trees have withered.The
        pomegranate trees, palm trees, and apple trees\u2014all the fruit trees\u2014have
        dried up.And the people\u2019s joy has dried up with them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Dress yourselves in burlap and weep, you priests!Wail, you who serve
        before the altar!Come, spend the night in burlap,you ministers of my God.For
        there is no grain or wineto offer at the Temple of your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Announce a time of fasting;call the people together for a solemn
        meeting.Bring the leadersand all the people of the landinto the Temple of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,and cry out to him there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is near,the day when destruction
        comes from the Almighty.How terrible that day will be!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Our food disappears before our very eyes.No joyful celebrations are
        held in the house of our God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The seeds die in the parched ground,and the grain crops fail.The
        barns stand empty,and granaries are abandoned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'How the animals moan with hunger!The herds of cattle wander about
        confused,because they have no pasture.The flocks of sheep and goats bleat
        in misery.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, help us!The fire has consumed the
        wilderness pastures,and flames have burned up all the trees.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Even the wild animals cry out to youbecause the streams have dried
        up,and fire has consumed the wilderness pastures.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Locusts Invade like an Army'
      title: Locusts Invade like an Army
      number: 1
      content: '  Sound the trumpet in Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]]!Raise the alarm on
        my holy mountain!Let everyone tremble in fearbecause the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is upon us.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion; </b>also in 2:15, 23.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'It is a day of darkness and gloom,a day of thick clouds and deep
        blackness.Suddenly, like dawn spreading across the mountains,a great and
        mighty army appears.Nothing like it has been seen beforeor will ever be seen
        again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Fire burns in front of them,and flames follow after them.Ahead of
        them the land liesas beautiful as the Garden of Eden.Behind them is nothing
        but desolation;not one thing escapes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They look like horses;they charge forward like warhorses.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:4 '
        content: Or <b>like charioteers.</b>
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Look at them as they leap along the mountaintops.Listen to the noise
        they make\u2014like the rumbling of chariots,like the roar of fire sweeping
        across a field of stubble,or like a mighty army moving into battle.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Fear grips all the people;every face grows pale with terror.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The attackers march like warriorsand scale city walls like soldiers.Straight
        forward they march,never breaking rank.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They never jostle each other;each moves in exactly the right position.They
        break through defenseswithout missing a step.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They swarm over the cityand run along its walls.They enter all the
        houses,climbing like thieves through the windows.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The earth quakes as they advance,and the heavens tremble.The sun
        and moon grow dark,and the stars no longer shine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: A Call to Repentance'
      title: A Call to Repentance
      number: 11
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is at the head of the column.He leads
        them with a shout.This is his mighty army,and they follow his orders.The
        day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is an awesome, terrible thing.Who
        can possibly survive?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "That is why the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says,\u201CTurn to me
        now, while there is time.Give me your hearts.Come with fasting, weeping,
        and mourning.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Don\u2019t tear your clothing in your grief,but tear your hearts
        instead.\u201DReturn to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,for he is
        merciful and compassionate,slow to get angry and filled with unfailing love.He
        is eager to relent and not punish.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Who knows? Perhaps he will give you a reprieve,sending you a blessing
        instead of this curse.Perhaps you will be able to offer grain and wineto
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God as before.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Blow the ram\u2019s horn in Jerusalem!Announce a time of fasting;call
        the people togetherfor a solemn meeting.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Gather all the people\u2014the elders, the children, and even the
        babies.Call the bridegroom from his quartersand the bride from her private
        room.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "17: The \u2019s Promise of Restoration"
      title: "The \u2019s Promise of Restoration"
      number: 17
      content: "Let the priests, who minister in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        presence,stand and weep between the entry room to the Temple and the altar.Let
        them pray, \u201CSpare your people, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Don\u2019t
        let your special possession become an object of mockery.Don\u2019t let them
        become a joke for unbelieving foreigners who say,\u2018Has the God of Israel
        left them?\u2019\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will pity his peopleand jealously
        guard the honor of his land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will reply,\u201CLook! I am sending
        you grain and new wine and olive oil,enough to satisfy your needs.You will
        no longer be an object of mockeryamong the surrounding nations.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "I will drive away these armies from the north.I will send them into
        the parched wastelands.Those in the front will be driven into the Dead Sea,and
        those at the rear into the Mediterranean.[[COMMENT(0)]]The stench of their
        rotting bodies will rise over the land.\u201DSurely the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has done great things!  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:20 '
        content: Hebrew <b>into the eastern sea, . . . into the western sea.</b>
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Don\u2019t be afraid, O land.Be glad now and rejoice,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has done great things.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Don\u2019t be afraid, you animals of the field,for the wilderness
        pastures will soon be green.The trees will again be filled with fruit;fig
        trees and grapevines will be loaded down once more.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Rejoice, you people of Jerusalem!Rejoice in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God!For the rain he sends demonstrates his faithfulness.Once more the
        autumn rains will come,as well as the rains of spring.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The threshing floors will again be piled high with grain,and the
        presses will overflow with new wine and olive oil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says, \u201CI will give you back
        what you lostto the swarming locusts, the hopping locusts,the stripping locusts,
        and the cutting locusts.[[COMMENT(0)]]It was I who sent this great destroying
        army against you.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:25 '
        content: 'The precise identification of the four kinds of locusts mentioned
          here is uncertain.  '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Once again you will have all the food you want,and you will praise
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,who does these miracles for you.Never
        again will my people be disgraced.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "27: The \u2019s Promise of His Spirit"
      title: "The \u2019s Promise of His Spirit"
      number: 27
      content: 'Then you will know that I am among my people Israel,that I am the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, and there is no other.Never again will
        my people be disgraced.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  [[COMMENT(0)]]\u201CThen, after doing all those things,I will pour
        out my Spirit upon all people.Your sons and daughters will prophesy.Your
        old men will dream dreams,and your young men will see visions.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:28 '
        content: '  Verses 2:28-32 are numbered 3:1-5 in Hebrew text.  '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "In those days I will pour out my Spiriteven on servants\u2014men
        and women alike.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And I will cause wonders in the heavens and on the earth\u2014blood
        and fire and columns of smoke.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The sun will become dark,and the moon will turn blood redbefore that
        great and terrible[[COMMENT(0)]] day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> arrives.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:31 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>glorious.</b>
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: But everyone who calls on the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>will
        be saved,for some on Mount Zion in Jerusalem will escape,just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has said.These will be among the survivorswhom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has called.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment against Enemy Nations'
      title: Judgment against Enemy Nations
      number: 1
      content: "    [[COMMENT(0)]]\u201CAt the time of those events,\u201D says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cwhen I restore the prosperity of Judah
        and Jerusalem,  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:1 '
        content: '  Verses 3:1-21 are numbered 4:1-21 in Hebrew text.  '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I will gather the armies of the worldinto the valley of Jehoshaphat.[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>There
        I will judge them</smallcaps>for harming my people, my special possession,for
        scattering my people among the nations,and for dividing up my land.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:2 '
        content: "<b>Jehoshaphat </b>means \u201Cthe <span class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">Lord</span>
          judges.\u201D"
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They threw dice[[COMMENT(0)]] to decide which of my peoplewould be
        their slaves.They traded boys to obtain prostitutesand sold girls for enough
        wine to get drunk.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:3 '
        content: Hebrew <b>They cast lots.</b>
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CWhat do you have against me, Tyre and Sidon and you cities
        of Philistia? Are you trying to take revenge on me? If you are, then watch
        out! I will strike swiftly and pay you back for everything you have done. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You have taken my silver and gold and all my precious treasures,
        and have carried them off to your pagan temples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You have sold the people of Judah and Jerusalem to the Greeks,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        so they could take them far from their homeland.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to the peoples of Javan.</b>
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBut I will bring them back from all the places to which you
        sold them, and I will pay you back for everything you have done. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I will sell your sons and daughters to the people of Judah, and they
        will sell them to the people of Arabia,[[COMMENT(0)]] a nation far away.
        I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to the Sabeans.</b>
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Say to the nations far and wide:\u201CGet ready for war!Call out
        your best warriors.Let all your fighting men advance for the attack.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Hammer your plowshares into swordsand your pruning hooks into spears.Train
        even your weaklings to be warriors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Come quickly, all you nations everywhere.Gather together in the valley.\u201DAnd
        now, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, call out your warriors!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CLet the nations be called to arms.Let them march to the valley
        of Jehoshaphat.There I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, will sitto pronounce
        judgment on them all.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Swing the sickle,for the harvest is ripe.[[COMMENT(0)]]Come, tread
        the grapes,for the winepress is full.The storage vats are overflowingwith
        the wickedness of these people.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:13 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>for the harvest time has come. </b>Compare
          Mark 4:29.
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Thousands upon thousands are waiting in the valley of decision.There
        the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will soon arrive.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The sun and moon will grow dark,and the stars will no longer shine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "16: Blessings for God\u2019s People"
      title: "Blessings for God\u2019s People"
      number: 16
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s voice will roar from Zionand
        thunder from Jerusalem,and the heavens and the earth will shake.But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will be a refuge for his people,a strong fortress for the people of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CThen you will know that I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God,live in Zion, my holy mountain.Jerusalem will be holy forever,and
        foreign armies will never conquer her again.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "In that day the mountains will drip with sweet wine,and the hills
        will flow with milk.Water will fill the streambeds of Judah,and a fountain
        will burst forth from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Temple,watering
        the arid valley of acacias.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:18 '
        content: Hebrew <b>valley of Shittim.</b>
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But Egypt will become a wastelandand Edom will become a wilderness,because
        they attacked the people of Judahand killed innocent people in their land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CBut Judah will be filled with people forever,and Jerusalem
        will endure through all generations.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I will pardon my people\u2019s crimes,which I have not yet pardoned;and
        I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, will make my homein Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]]
        with my people.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '3:21 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
